ution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Woodcock was born about 1175, in Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1175–":"umbes 1175–Surnud","1216–Male":"1216–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","Abt 1175":"umbes 1175","1216":"1216","1175":"1175","Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Leyland, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1175–":"noin 1175–Kuollut","1216–Male":"1216–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","Abt 1175":"noin 1175","1216":"1216","1175":"1175","Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Leyland, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1175–":"environ 1175–Décédé","1216–Male":"1216–Décédé","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","Abt 1175":"environ 1175","1216":"1216","1175":"1175","Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Leyland, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Woodcock est né environ 1175, à Leyland, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1175–":"um 1175–Verstorben","1216–Male":"1216–Verstorben","1175–Male":"1175–Verstorben","Abt 1175":"um 1175","1216":"1216","1175":"1175","Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William Woodcock wurde um 11